# Instinct RPG — Quick Reference (v2)

**Live file:** `instinct-rpg-quick-ref-v2.html` — Card Studio **Quick Ref** tab (`index.html` iframe).
**Retired:** `instinct-rpg-quick-ref.html` (DC, Flaws, full Contest procedure — do not use).

## Role vs Player Primer

| Asset | When | Format |
|-------|------|--------|
| **Player Primer v2** | Before session — read once | Long, dark, examples + FAQ |
| **Quick Ref v2** | During session — glance / print | Narrow (~440px), light, dense rows |

Quick Ref is **lookup**, not onboarding. No chargen walkthrough, no FAQ accordion, no card samples.

## Content scope

**Include:** golden rule, deck/hand one-liner, Build/Roll/Read, tier base dice, Miss/Crit/Toll/Flourish,
clear-pool rules, Aid, Boost, success vs partial, Hit Dice, card-type chips, Trigger reminder,
conditions as shared vocabulary (GM decides), scene hand pacing.

**Defer (one box only):** Resolve, Threat, Contests, Snap Check — “GM teaches when it comes up.”

**Never:** DC language, Flaws, self-discard Boost, mechanical condition auto-rules, full Contest
procedure, Scar/knockout loops unless doctrine promotes them to pre-read.

## Alignment

Must match `design/core-rules.md` and `instinct-rpg-primer-v2.html` rhetoric. When checks or Aid
change, update **doctrine → primer → quick ref** in that order.

